FILES:
(1) lab1a.c
	Implememnting:
	--rdonly f
		Open the read-only file. No flags.
	--wronly f
		Open the write-only file. No flags.
	--verbose
		Print the processing command.
	--command i o e cmd args
		Execute cmd with stdin to i, stdout to o, stderr to e.

(2) Makefile
	'make check' contains 5 test cases:
	1. invalid file indices
	2. less than 3 file indices
	3. wrong subcommand option
	4. unreadable file
	5. insufficient arguments after --command

LIMITATIONS:
(1) The program does not check the exit status of the subcommand.
(2) The program will ignore wrong usage of --rdonly, --wronly, --verbose,
	e.g. parsing multiple arguments after the option.

TESTING:
The program has only been tested on SEASnet server 9.
